CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Selling Carver Seals - The committee in charge of the annual sales of George Washington Carver Seals officially opened the drive in office of Mayor David L. Lawrence last Thursday. In the photo are (left to right): Mayor Lawrence, Mrs. Alma Illery, Mrs. S. F. Wilkerson, Mrs. Mary Clark, Mrs. Jessie Bolden, chairmans of the campaign, and Mrs. Eunice Cook. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Mayor David L. Lawrence, Alma Illery, S. F. Wilkerson, Mary Clark holding George Washington Carver Seals with Lawrence, Jessie Bolden, Eunice Cook, and man, standing in mayor's office, another version
